Well, I wanted a regular pretzel with cinnamon sugar. Unfortunately they didn't have any pretzels period to dip into the sugar. I was asked if I minded waiting and I said no. They then made a whole batch of pretzels and then they were about to hand me two regular pretzels. They ended up blaming it on the guy that took my order who had left for the day shortly after taking my order. So I was asked yet again if I minded waiting and I again said no.  During this whole ordeal I watched them burn an entire batch of pretzels and they threw them all into the garbage. It took so long to get me a cinnamon pretzel, they offered me a drink of my choosing. I eventually received my pretzel.  The wait time had to be at least half an hour. 8:15-8:45pm. Should have been offered a refund as well but, Meh.

To be fair the food itself was good. The service is where the ball dropped from the second floor of the mall into the basement floor. It was terrible because I spoke to the cashier and said hi how are you today? They did not acknowledge my existence, I thought maybe they did not hear me. I put in my order and my wife is a rewards member. She asked how the points worked and not only did the cashier have no idea, the staff lead who was there rudely said ring them up and make them scan thier rewards at the end. This was a very poor display of customer service that I observed others after me experienced.  It takes a lot for me to not recommend a place but do yourself a favor and explore other food options at this mall.

I love Aunt Anne’s. However the person working this afternoon had a terrible attitude. She could’ve just been having a bad day. But don’t let that show in your customer service. Body language 100% showed she did not want to stop what she was doing to help me, (I’m sure that’s why the people in front of me decided to leave) it was rude, and the pretzel I received was charred. I didn’t say anything because it was still edible, and I didn’t want to exert the energy to make it a big deal. I understand that bad days can happen,  I Hope her day gets better; or if she doesn’t want to work there then just don’t.
